<br>
I would hope this has made me wiser and more understanding of the game we all love, and not just 213 days 18 hours 38 minutes older.  I remember resisting the call of Everquest through much of the first age, only barely before Kunark was discovered did I partake of the world of Norrath.<br>
<br>
I remember trembling before the might of the cruchbone orcs who under the influence of the dark elves still threaten the homelands of the Faydark and Felwithian elves.  I still intend to return there one day and display the power I have mastered in my travels, ensuring the safety of my homeland.<br>
<br>
This community of mages helped me immeasurably in my early explorations.  The discussions here are an invaluable gauge of our class.  From the frenzy leading to and during caster balancing through the calmer times we seem to have entered many ideas have surfaced and emerged in-game as a result of this board.<br>
<br>
Who would have imagined that pets would be indifferent, that pet commands would finally be zone wide and that we would arguably regain our status as the second best nuker in the game.  It may be painfully slow but SoE/VI has listened to the majority of ours and other classes suggestions and complaints.<br>
<br>
Now, that doesn't mean everything is perfect.  Nothing ever will be in everyones eyes, but there is light at the end of the tunnel.  We are as powerful as we ever were, for we tread on the Planes of Power and the gods themselves tremble.  Enjoy being a Magician and rejoice in our resurgence! <p><hr>
