<br>
Our pets do excellent damage, any more would be a bit much.. The nukes we have are good and solid, then we have situational nukes that can boost our DPS even more in certain circumstances (Rains + bolts).  We arent a support class anymore yet we retain the ability to summon an entire raid rods which is useful<br>
<br>
There are still problems of course, namely I still dont like how our mez caps at 65 although I can live with charm being capped low since it's rather powerful.. Servant of Ro is still completely pathetic and needs to be looked at<br>
<br>
Also the spell drop rate in tier1/2 zones needs to be looked at ESPECIALLY in regards to spectrals, but other than that being a mage is very fun now.. My damage is respected and I have a unique damage role no other class can duplicate.  As i've said in other posts the Mage class is the best at taking punishment 1v1 with a mob with no helpers and that's nothing to be taken lightly <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/YlaineEQ/fullsize/cheersig2.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
