<br>
While a mages ability to solo exp mobs dwindles significantly with levels, we make up for it in terms of raw damage, and therefore group desirability.<br>
<br>
Even against mobs that hit in the high 300s to low 400s, Jobaner is a very effective tank, especially if the mob is slowed. I charm-kite with an enchanter all the time now, and when charm breaks you bet your ass its my pet tanking the mob (60% enchanter-haste mind you) until its recharmed. Whenever I go LFG, I am constantly bugged by Trials groups (and for some odd reason always invited to Ixiblat raids. /boggle)<br>
<br>
If you can't find a group, improvise and make your own. Full balanced groups are nice, but small duos or trios, or even pet groups are extremely fun and enjoyable. This is true from level 1 to level 65.<br>
<br>
And yes, I still get bothered for Mod Rods in groups and raids. Guess other classes like it for the long-term mana regen too.<br>
<br>
