<br>
The evening that I completed my quest for the Orb of Mastery, I returned to the Faydark and drank myself into a sodden stupor rejoicing in the completion of my seemingly lifelong quest.<br>
<br>
In the morning I heard tales of a mighty mage in a brilliant red robe who had run rampant through Crushbone wielding a mighty swirling orb and a huge Air pet that made the Crushbone Orcs flee in terror.<br>
<br>
/ooc that was such a blast.  I was drunk as hell in RL and wandered through CB killing everything, helping the players with trains, killing Dvinn and the other high level mobs and giving away their stuff.  I maxed out my factions that night... /grin<br>
<br>
I agree that the mage has changed alot since I started playing.  My first character (now deleted) was a mage and was born in Dec of 1999.  Arkelon was born in Jan 2000.  I did not make 60 until the week before PoP came out.<br>
<br>
I have seen all of the changes.  I remember when VI made it so that pet's poofed when invis to undead was cast on you.  I remember the uber use of sword of runes, because it procced against everything, not just summoned creatures.<br>
<br>
I enjoy playing a magician.  I have my problems with the one-dimensional nature of the classes in general, not from a functional standpoint but from an enjoyment standpoint.  I get tired of doing the same thing... that is why we have alts, right?<br>
<br>
I do believe that VI has made many positive changes to the mage class, making us both more fun to play, and more desirable in groups.<br>
<br>
/ooc off<br>
<br>
/salute my fellow magicians<br>
<br>
Respectfully,<br>
Arkelon Alkarinque<br>
